        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_CleanseNewFiscalYearPrerequisiteData",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to delete records from several tables within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Preload",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema that are associated with a specific fiscal year ("
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "FY",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "). This procedure is intended to reset or cleanse data related to a new fiscal year, allowing a wizard or process to be repeated without interference from existing data."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving simple DELETE operations on multiple tables based on a single condition. There are no complex joins, subqueries, or conditional logic, which keeps the complexity low."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
